# Beacon Web Design

## Colors

Never use hard-coded hex values in components. Always reference a CSS custom property from `tokens.css`.

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
color: var(--color-text-primary);

/* ❌ BAD */
color: #FAFAFA;
```

## Health Scores

Always use the `HealthScoreBadge` component. Never render a score as a plain number styled inline.

## Icons

Always import from `lucide-react`. Standard sizes are 16px (sm), 20px (md), 24px (lg). No other icon sources.

## Spacing

Use Tailwind utility classes (`p-4`, `gap-6`, etc.) which map to the 4px base scale. Avoid arbitrary values like `p-[18px]`.

## Dark Mode

Never use Tailwind's `dark:` prefix. All theme variation is handled by CSS custom properties in `tokens.css`. Components work in both themes automatically.

## Typography

Use the semantic text tokens for key elements:

- `text-5xl font-bold` — score numbers
- `text-lg font-semibold` — account names
- `text-sm` — labels and captions

## Components

Reuse existing components from `src/components/ui/` before creating new ones. Check what exists before building.

## Animation

Keep transitions under 200ms. Use `ease-out`. No bouncy springs on data — only on celebratory/feedback moments.
